description:
Wildlife - Episode 3: Just Reptiles | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Wildlife - Episode 4' here: https://youtu.be/SNRyvGzDsww

Wrapped up in myths and misunderstandings, “cold-blooded” Reptiles are a diverse group with thousands of species crawling, slithering, and swimming the planet. While Crocodilians, Turtles, and Tortoises were featured in Series One, the main focus in Series Two and this episode is on snakes and lizards, plus the enigmatic Tuatara of New Zealand. Go beyond the forked tongues and fangs and discover more about these intriguing, striking animals. Venture out for a wild time with devils, vipers, monsters, and dragons.

Experience the wonder of captivating documentaries in this engaging series, exploring the lives and behaviors of some of the planet's most incredible animals. From Monkeys and Penguins to Sharks, Marsupials, Wild Cats, Reptiles, Wild Dogs, Insects, Hooved Mammals, and Octopuses, each episode delves into the world of a specific group, providing a thorough exploration of their fascinating existence. Enjoy a visual feast with high-quality archive footage, showcasing rare behaviors, intimate close-ups, and fast-paced action sequences. Uncover the extraordinary physical attributes, sensory perceptions, communication skills, and ingenious adaptations of a diverse array of creatures, both great and small.
